<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Penaherrera-Leiva" box="[341,783,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" refString="Penaherrera-Leiva, A. Y. &amp; Tavakilian, G. L. (2004) Nouvelles especes et nouveaux genres de Rhinotragini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). III. Coleopteres, 10 (10), 119 - 150." type="journal article" year="2004">
Peñaherrera-Leiva &amp; Tavakilian (
<number box="[716,775,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
distinguished 
<taxonomicName box="[946,1035,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingae">
<emphasis box="[946,1035,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. ingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1050,1131,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,1119,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,1106,1912]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15, Phygopoda ingae Peñaherrera-Leiva &amp; Tavakilian, 2004, female holotype; 16, Phygopoda fulvitarsis Gounelle, 1911, male lectotype; 17, Phygopoda fugax Thomson, 1864, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234413/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1102,1131,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) from 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1297,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugax">
<emphasis box="[1207,1297,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. fugax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1312,1393,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,1119,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,1106,1912]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15, Phygopoda ingae Peñaherrera-Leiva &amp; Tavakilian, 2004, female holotype; 16, Phygopoda fulvitarsis Gounelle, 1911, male lectotype; 17, Phygopoda fugax Thomson, 1864, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234413/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1364,1393,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) by the elytra with a constriction at the apical fifth. This feature distinguishes it not only from 
<emphasis box="[1156,1242,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. f ugax</emphasis>
but also from all other species of the genus, except 
<taxonomicName box="[535,675,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvitarsis">
<emphasis box="[535,675,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. fulvitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[691,771,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,1119,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,1106,1912]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 15 – 17. 15, Phygopoda ingae Peñaherrera-Leiva &amp; Tavakilian, 2004, female holotype; 16, Phygopoda fulvitarsis Gounelle, 1911, male lectotype; 17, Phygopoda fugax Thomson, 1864, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234413/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[743,771,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1212,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvitarsis">
<emphasis box="[1072,1212,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. fulvitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the elytra with a constriction at the apical fifth and a brush of setae of different colors on the apical third. 
<taxonomicName box="[1153,1293,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvitarsis">
<emphasis box="[1153,1293,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. fulvitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,240,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingae">
<emphasis box="[151,240,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. ingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the color of the setae on the apical forth of the brush, yellowish in 
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1166,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvitarsis">
<emphasis box="[1027,1166,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. fulvitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(whitish in 
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1390,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phygopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingae">
<emphasis box="[1300,1390,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">P. ingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
